In large bowl mix together crushed cereal, sugar, flour, cocoa, salt and pecans. Add oil, eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix just until combined. Spread evenly in 33x23 cm (13x9-inch) baking pan. Bake at 180 degrees C (350 degrees F) about 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in centre comes out clean. (Do not overbake.) Cool completely on wire rack before cutting into squares. Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.